>> Access Specifiers are used to provide the visibiltiy of the members

>>There are four Access Specifiers
    1.public
    2.Protected
    3.default
    4.private


>>If we want universal access we can go for public

>>If we wanted to give access to all generations
    parent
    child
    another child class from another package

>>If we wanted to give access to line up gernerations
    parent
    child

>If we dont want anyone to access directly
    parent